# Mock monitored stream — ~8 communications/transactions, some violating, some routine.
# One JSON object per line (blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored by the loader).
#
# Schema:
#   id      : stable item id
#   channel : where it came from (email | chat | txn) — informational
#   text    : the content the screener reads (and retrieves a policy rule against)
#   amount  : numeric USD amount for transaction items (null for comms) — fed to the anomaly check
#   expected: the label a compliance reviewer assigned (clear | flag) — used only to sanity-check the demo
#
# This is the file you replace with a connector to your real monitored streams (comms, txns, access logs).
